Despite a walkout on Wednesday, Parliament&#8217;s portfolio ad hoc committee says it will continue with its proceedings as planned today. CAPE TOWN It s the second day of a parliamentary inquiry into the fitness of the one-man South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) board.The SABC delegation, including Group CEO James Aguma and executive Hlaudi Motsoeneng, staged a walkout on Wednesday, while the only remaining board member, chairperson Mbulaheni Maguvhe, filed for leave to appeal a high court ruling which dismissed his previous application to halt the investigation.Parliament's ad hoc committee will sit for 11 days as it looks into the board's affairs and Maguvhe s fitness to hold office.Despite disruptions, Parliament s portfolio ad hoc committee says it will continue with its proceedings as planned today.WATCH LIVE: SABC board inquiry proceeds(Edited by Shimoney Regter)